      %article.javascript.tabbed-content-tab
        .padding
          %h1.gamma.extra-bold-weight JavaScript
          .column-one
            %p.epsilon JavaScript is, without doubt, the most challenging and, at times, frustrating part of my job. Having said that, I also find it the most rewarding.
            %p I've found that the way I write my code has changed greatly over the past year, and thanks to tools such as ESLint and Jasmine I've been able to refactor previous work and approach it slightly differently.
            %p I have worked on a number of projects, each utilising different libraries, so I have been exposed to several of the front-runners. With the current state of JavaScript and the "flavour of the week" scenario that we are facing, I am currently focused on making sure that my base knowledge of vanilla JavaScript is as sound as possible.
            %p
              I have written a number of
              = link_to "vanilla JavaScript modules", "https://www.npmjs.com/~ianhatton"
              which are in use across several of my recent projects.

